From 73342eeccd1cb4bcfc2a79ca486f39f6affad16c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 21:26:14 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Rewrite scanner with malware classification, interactive
 menu, colored output

- 16 malware types: cryptominer, botnet, C2 server, RAT, backdoor,
  rootkit, DDoS bot, IRC bot, webshell, dropper, worm, stealer,
  ransomware, proxy, suspicious, unknown
- Signature-based classification using cmdline + exe path matching
- Severity levels: CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW per malware type
- Color-coded ANSI output with ASCII art banner
- 4-phase flow: scan -> threat analysis summary -> detailed findings -> action menu
- Interactive remediation menu with 7 options:
  [1] Review each finding individually (per-finding action submenu)
  [2-5] Graduated auto-remediation (kill -> +block -> +quarantine -> +cron)
  [6] Full aggression (all above + exploit C2 + poison sockets)
  [0] Exit without action
- Per-finding actions: kill PID, kill group, poison socket, block IP,
  exploit C2, quarantine file, strip cron
- CLI flags still work: -r -E -P -B -G -q for non-interactive use
- Findings stored in array for summary stats before action phase
